# HelmKit Licensing

The HelmKit repository is multi-licensed by content type. The full text of each
license is included in this repository.

| Content type | Path globs | License | SPDX identifier | License file |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Source code** (firmware, host software, build scripts, CI) | `firmware/**`, `software/**`, `tools/**`, `scripts/**`, `.github/**`, root-level scripts | GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 | `AGPL-3.0-or-later` | [`LICENSE-code.txt`](LICENSE-code.txt) |
| **Hardware design** (mechanical CAD, PCB sources, BOMs, fabrication outputs) | `3D-Models/**`, `hardware/**`, `**/*.step`, `**/*.stl`, `**/*.f3d`, `**/*.kicad_pcb`, `**/*.kicad_sch`, `**/*.kicad_pro`, `**/*.gbr`, `**/*.drl`, `**/bom.csv` | CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 — Strongly Reciprocal | `CERN-OHL-S-2.0` | [`LICENSE-hardware.txt`](LICENSE-hardware.txt) |
| **Documentation, theory, specifications** (`docs/`, READMEs, this file) | `docs/**`, `**/*.md` (other than license/notice files), `experiments/**/*.md`, `**/README.md` | Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International | `CC-BY-SA-4.0` | [`LICENSE-docs.txt`](LICENSE-docs.txt) |
| **Third-party content** | as marked in `external/` and `iOS_oldBuild/Frameworks/` | per original license | (varies) | per submodule |

## SPDX tagging

Source files SHOULD include an SPDX header on the first or second line. Examples:

```c
// SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
```

```python
# SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
```

```text
SPDX-License-Identifier: CERN-OHL-S-2.0
```

```markdown
<!-- SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0 -->
```

Files lacking an explicit SPDX header are governed by the path-glob mapping above.

## Trademarks

**HelmKit™** is an unregistered trademark of Jordan Trana, claimed by first use
in commerce on this public repository. See [`NOTICE.md`](NOTICE.md).

The names of associated Psi-Tech presets and modules ("Psi Stabilizer™",
"Psi Harmonizer™", "Psi Defender™") are similarly claimed as unregistered
marks where used in this repository to identify HelmKit-substrate products.

Use of these marks to identify products or services other than those produced
by the HelmKit project requires written permission. Nominative or descriptive
use (e.g., comparative review, academic discussion, interoperability
documentation) is permitted under standard trademark fair-use principles.

The licenses above grant rights in copyright and (where applicable) patent;
they do **not** grant any right to use the HelmKit trademarks.

## Patent posture

The HelmKit project explicitly disclaims any intent to assert patents against
implementers of this design. The AGPL-3.0 and CERN-OHL-S-2.0 licenses both
contain express patent grants; any contribution to this repository is made
under those terms.

This repository is also intended as **defensive publication**: see
[`PRIOR_ART.md`](PRIOR_ART.md) for the prior-art declaration and inventory of
disclosed inventive elements.

## Why these choices

- **AGPL-3.0** for code: strong copyleft including the network-use clause.
  Anyone who runs a modified HelmKit firmware or back-end as a service must
  release the modifications. Blocks closed-source clones in cloud form.
- **CERN-OHL-S-2.0** for hardware: the strongly-reciprocal variant of the
  CERN Open Hardware Licence. Manufacturers who ship modified HelmKit hardware
  must release their modifications under the same license. This is the
  standard for open hardware projects with copyleft intent (cf. the Open
  Source Hardware Association recommendation list).
- **CC-BY-SA-4.0** for docs: the Wikipedia-compatible share-alike copyleft for
  prose, schematics-as-images, and explanatory diagrams. Anyone who publishes
  a derivative wiki, book, or training corpus must release the result under
  the same terms.

The combination is engineered so that a hostile fork that omits attribution,
closes the source, or relicenses the docs is in license violation in at least
one of the three channels — and a fork that complies with all three is, by
definition, an open, attributed contribution to the HelmKit ecosystem.
